icn-youtube-30x30.png" id="video-rectangle" data-embed-type="video" data-ref-id="2300-6464338" data-src="/videos/perfect-dark-gameplay-reveal-trailer-xbox-games-showcase-2024/2300-6464338/" data-width="100%" data-height="100%" data-video-start="0"><div><p>Perfect Dark Gameplay Reveal Trailer | Xbox Games Showcase 2024</p><div><p>         Want us to remember this setting for all your devices?       </p><p><a href="https://www.gamespot.com/signup/">Sign up</a> or <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/login/">Sign in</a> now!       </p></div></div><p>       Please use a html5 video capable browser to watch videos.     </p><p>       This video has an invalid file format.     </p><p>Sorry, but you can't access this content!</p></div><p dir="ltr">The former Insomniac developer previously served on Marvel's Spider-Man: Miles Morales, too, but apparently creative differences led to Horton no longer working on Wolverine. That wasn't the only change either, as Cameron Christian is no longer directing the PS5 game (though it's noted that Christian is staying at Insomniac).</p><p dir="ltr">In their place now is the leadership duo behind <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/reviews/ratchet-clank-rift-apart-review-a-riveting-adventure/1900-6417686/" data-ref-id="1900-6417686">Ratchet &amp; Clank: Rift Apart</a>, <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/the-best-playstation-exclusive-games-of-2021/1100-6498986/" data-ref-id="1100-6498986">one of the best PlayStation games of 2021</a>. Mike Daly has taken over as game director for Wolverine, with Marcus Smith on as creative director.</p><p dir="ltr">Neither game has an official release window. <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/insomniac-ps5-spider-man-and-wolverine-are-in-the-same-universe-dev-confirms/1100-6518742/" data-ref-id="1100-6518742">Wolverine does take place in the same universe as Spider-Man</a> on PS5, but other than that, not much is known. However, do be aware that <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/psa-marvels-wolverine-spoilers-are-spreading-after-insomniac-hack/1100-6520040/" data-ref-id="1100-6520040">spoilers for Wolverine spread on the internet after the Insomniac hack</a> last year. Meanwhile, <a href="https://www.gamespot.com/articles/perfect-dark-gets-first-gameplay-trailer/1100-6524084/" data-ref-id="1100-6524084">Perfect Dark got its first gameplay trailer</a> in June at the Xbox Games Showcase. It's a single-player game with an emphasis on parkour, gadgets, and spying.</p>
  
                        
    
        
        
  
